==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: zip code
<hw>zip" code`</hw> <pr>(z⟦icr⟧p"k⟦omac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>z</ets>one <ets>i</ets>mprovement <ets>p</ets>lan.]</ety>
<def>Any one of a set of numbers assigned by the <org>United States
Postal Service</org> to designate a particular postal delivery area. One
or more <ex>zip codes</ex> are assigned to each post office. The numbers
initially had five digits (the <part>initial code</part>), indicating
state and post office. Later, four more optional digits were added (the
<part>expanded code</part>) indicating the box number or delivery route.
The full set of nine digits is also referred to as <stype>zip +
4</stype>. The code is appended in an address to the line bearing the
city and state names, as in ⟦ldquo⟧Plainfield, NJ 07062⟦rdquo⟧.</def>
<altsp>[Also spelled <asp>ZIP code</asp> and <asp>Zip
code</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>zip-code</ent>⟦br⟧
